post: {'type': 'pro', 'text': "Prohibition clearly isn't enough either, and all but ensures that honest education and information becomes impossible, making it exaggerated and ineffective."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "It is unlikely that a low level drug dealer will shift to trafficking human beings the moment drugs get legalised. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The US government has [previously supported](https://www.ozy.com/flashback/when-the-government-said-marijuana-made-you-crazy/88232) the claim that marijuana use causes individuals to rape and murder others, or commit suicide. {'type': 'pro', 'text': "When weed was legalized in Colorado for recreational use, the [usage rate](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-colorado-marijuana-idUSKCN0Z702N) among teens and children stayed the same. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Through education, heavy advertising campaigns and controlling the packaging of tobacco, the government can make its negative effects clear despite it being legal. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The risk of MDMA is not higher than many sports. MDMA has been compared to [horseback riding](http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/uk/7876425.stm) in terms of risks. That's why all drugs should be legal."}

I believe all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization of drugs will make people aware of their consequences \\(having a prospectus like medicine with known pros and cons - like marijuana for medical usage\\). So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'People who want to use drugs are largely already able to get access to them, but can have no assurance about their safety or quality. Government regulations could resolve this problem. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drug use has a negative effect on freedom and, therefore, ought to be contained.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The risk of unknown purity and poor-quality drugs will be minimized. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug use will not cease regardless of the legal status. I think all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The number of deaths from overdose will rise dramatically as a result of easy access to drugs including meth, MDMA, and heroin. So legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drug prohibition might be inspired by some kind of racism but abandoning it would not necessarily mean an improvement of the situation for those incarcerated or addicted to drugs. There are still many other systematic racial issues unrelated to drug prohibition.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Even a year after release, former convicts [are 10-18 times more likely](https://sph.unc.edu/sph-news/former-inmates-at-high-risk-for-opioid-overdose-following-prison-release/) to die of an overdose than the average population.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will make it easier for researchers to study how different illicit drugs affect our brain and thereby advance our understanding of neuroscience.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'When the government legalizes something, it \\(unintentionally\\) sends the message that the substance is acceptable and a legitimate form of recreation. This may encourage people to become involved in drug taking.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'If the primary goal is defeating drug dealing and cartels, the most effective way would be just ceasing drug use by everyone. With the "added bonus" that without drug use people will also be healthier and richer. I think drugs should remain illegal.'}
